javascriptText:
// Initialize our picture
initPicture(-2.3,5.3,-3.3,4.3)

// Set the fontsize large for the axes
fontsize=25
axes(1, 1, "labels", 1)

// Set a thick blue stroke
strokewidth = "2"
stroke = "blue"
// Plot our piecewise linear function as a series of lines
line([-3, -3], [2, 1])
line([2, 3], [6, -2])
// Add some filled in and empty dots
fontsize=19
fontfill="red"
dotradius=5
dot([2,1], "open")
dot([2,3], "open")
dot([2,2], "closed", 'Discontinuity!', 'aboveleft')
description: Piecewise linear with dots and a label specifying the behavior at the discontinuity.
